A 32-year-old, Akeem Ayoade, on Monday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court, for allegedly stealing N608,000. Ayoade, whose address was not provided, is being tried for stealing. He, however, pleaded not guilty. The Prosecutor, Insp. Victor Eruada, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on April 1, at Salako Street, Aluminum Village, Dopemu, Lagos. Eruada said that Ayoade stole money belonging to Aluminum Profile and Glass Association (APGA). “Ayoade collected and stole the N608,000 from a customer who came to purchase products, as he presented himself as the owner of the company,” the prosecutor said. Eruada said the offence contravened Section 287 of Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The Magistrate, M.I. Dan-Oni, granted the defendant a bail of N200, 000 with two sureties in like sum, and adjourned the case until May 21. (NAN)